Description: Gibson Corvus 1 Vintage 1983 Electric Guitar w/Original Hardshell Case. Condition is Used. Shipped with USPS Parcel Select Ground. If you saw this picture and thought, “What the heck is that?!” then you’re not alone. What you are looking at is a very rare guitar called a Gibson Corvus I. These guitars were only made between 1982-1984 I and look like a cross between a can-opener and a battle axe. This particular guitar is from 1983 (according to the Guitar Center Vintage Team). This one is a Corvus I. It has one humbucker pick-up, a volume control and tone control. The neck shows some wear and could use a little TLC, but everything works and is original! This guitar is actually a “factory second” and is stamped as such on the back of the neck. The reason being is that the guitar was produced and came out of the factory with a split in the body. You can see it in the pictures. Barely visible from the front and does not affect playability. I’ve always thought it gave it character. Comes with a custom fitted Gibson hardshell case perfectly fitted for this guitar. The case is pretty dinged up, but it’s what you’d expect of a 35 year old guitar case. The handle on the case has been replaced. Parting out my collection of guitars to save for some new ones. This is hard to let go of, but it’s your chance to own a piece of guitar history! Shipping only within the contiguous 48 states. Buyer pays min $80 s/h (could be more if shipping ends up being more).
Title: Gibson Corvus 1 Vintage 1983 Electric Guitar w/Original Hardshell Case
